\lim_{n\to\infty}{\frac{3n+1}{2n+5}=\frac{3}{2}}
\mid{\frac{3n+1}{2n+5}-\frac{3}{2}}\mid=\mid{\frac{6n+2}{4n+10}-\frac{6n+15}{4n+10}}\mid= \mid\frac{-13}{4n+10}\mid=\frac{13}{4n+10}<\frac{13}{4n}<\frac{13}{n}<\epsilon
\frac{13}{n}
\epsilon >0
\frac{1}{\epsilon}>0\implies \frac{13}{\epsilon}
k\in\mathbb{N}
\frac{13}{\epsilon}<k\implies \frac{13}{k}<\epsilon
\epsilon >0
\frac{1}{\epsilon}>0\implies \frac{13}{\epsilon}>0
k\in\mathbb{N}
k>\frac{13}{\epsilon}\implies \frac{13}{k}<\epsilon
n \geq k
\frac{1}{n} \leq \frac{1}{k}\implies \frac{13}{n}\leq \frac{13}{k} <\epsilon
\mid{\frac{3n+1}{2n+5}-\frac{3}{2}}\mid<\frac{13}{n}<\epsilon
\lim{\frac{3n+1}{2n+5}=\frac{3}{2}}
